author: jdillon
msg: Simplify the 'set' command by not going with the 'set a=b' syntax, instead using 'set a b' or 'set a "b c d e"'.  This removes some hacks to deal with quoting.  May bring the = stuff back once the parser can handle it.

author: thorsten
msg: Extracting common method that can be used in both implementations.
addProperties method has enhanced the properties treatment.
Before if in xmlProperties mode we always created a dom object even if the property only contained a @value and no childs.
Now in this case we will fall back to the @value and passing a string.
